British Petroleum Co PLC said it hasstarted its previously announced 7.4 billion dlr offer topurchase the 45 pct interest in Standard Oil Co that it doesnot already own for 70 dlrs per share.    In a newspaper advertisement, the company said the offer,which is not conditioned on receipt of any minimum number ofshares, and associated withdrawal rights will expire April 28unless extended.    BP said it is asking Standard Oil for the use of itsshareholder list in disseminating the offer, on which theStandard board has not yet taken a position. Reuter&#3;